Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and boil your #kettle{}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press). Halve, peel and slice the @onion{1}(peeled and sliced) into thin half moons. Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1}(halved, cored and chopped into roughly 1cm chunks) and @red pepper{1}(halved, cored and chopped into roughly 1cm chunks). Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a #colander{}. Peel and chop the @potato{1}(peeled and chopped into ½cm pieces). Roughly chop the @coriander{½%sprig}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest the @lime{½%lime}(zested, then cut into wedges for later), then cut into wedges for later.

Put a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the onion. Cook gently until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the peppers and cook until slightly soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Add the potato and cook for another ~{2%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @Mexican spice{½}(fajita seasoning) and @smoked paprika{1.5%tsp}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more. TIP: Some like it hot, but if that's not you just use less of the fajita spice blend. Next, add the mixed beans and @tomato passata{1%tin}.

Add the @vegetable stock pot{1} together with the boiling @water{½%cup} and stir to dissolve. Bring the soup to a gentle simmer. Simmer until the potato is cooked, around ~{10-15%minutes}. Tip: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Meanwhile, rub a very light coating of @olive oil{a light coating} on both sides of each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{2}. Slice into long, 1cm wide strips. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then place on a #baking tray{} and cook on the middle shelf of your oven until really crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Watch them like a hawk as they'll burn easily! Put the @sour cream{½%tsp} in a #small bowl{} and add half the lime zest. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Taste and add more zest to your liking.

Just before serving, stir in half the coriander. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Serve in #bowls{}, topped with a dollop of zesty sour cream and a sprinkling of the remaining coriander. Put some crispy tortilla strips and a lime wedge on the side. TIP: Make sure you get plenty of the chunky veggies in each bowl so no one misses out! Get slurping!